name: Transcon_GC_DC_IC_MCCOST
description:
Create a happy path end-to-end automation script that runs in the given QA Environments without errors.
  •Origin - QA3/VRN
  •Gateway1- QA1/DEN
  •Gateway2 - QA9/MSY
  •Destination - QA4/YYC

  NOTE:

  • While processing shipments, enter amounts into every costs field/s available (charge/rates)
  • In case of prepaid, rate and bill can be in different currencies. Example rate in local currency (AWBHDR screen) and bill in foreign currency (INV screen)
  •In case of collect, rate and bill should be in same currency. Example rate in local currency (AWBHDR screen) and bill should be in local currency as well (INV screen) or vice versa

  Steps:

  1.Process a prepaid house truck shipment from origin to destination. Rate in local currency (EUR) and bill in foreign currency (CAD)
  2.Process a prepaid house truck shipment from origin to destination. Rate and bill in foreign currency (CAD)
  3.Process EHT shipment to INV
  4. Create invoice that has a mix of freight revenue GL's, billing codes mapped to freight revenue and other GL's not mapped to freight revenue
  5.Finish the shipments by printing on AWBPRT
  6.Confirm CFDATA is clear in Origin
  7.In Origin consol screen, attach the HBLs to GC destined to gateway1
  8.Process upto MNFST then print
  9.In Export Origin find on GC reference in DCCOST screen
  10.Enter amount in the DC Origin Transfer field, and then hit F1/Post
  11.Confirm CFDATA is clear in Origin
  12.In Export gateway1 find on DC reference in DCLOG screen
  13.Enter DC Destin Cost, and the rest of the fields, and then hit F1/Add Modify
  14.Confirm CFDATA is clear in gateway1
  15. Process a prepaid house truck shipment from gateway1 to final destination. Rate and bill in local currency (USD)
  16.In gateway1 consol, attach the original HBL and a new prepaid house truck shipment to a DC destined to gateway2
  17.Process upto MNFST and hit F1/Add Modify
  18.In Export gateway1 find on DC reference in DCCOST screen
  19.Enter amount in the DC Origin Transfer field, and then hit F1/Post
  20.In Export gateway2 find on DC reference in DCLOG screen
  21.Enter DC Destin Cost, and the rest of the fields, and then hit F1/Add Modify
  22.Confirm CFDATA is clear in gateway2
  23.Process a collect house truck shipment from gateway2 to final destination. Rate in local currency (USD) and bill in foreign currency (CAD)
  24.In gateway2 consol, attach the original HBLs and collect house truck shipment to an IC destined to final destination
  25.Process MNFST, ICCOST, HBCOST and post MCTRAN
  26.Confim CFDATA is clear in gateway2
  27.Receive ShipLog at CFIT destination and post the consol settlement

  EHT1 prepaid VRN - YYC (rate and bill in local currency (EUR) and bill in foreign currency (CAD))
  EHT2 prepaid VRN - YYC (rate and bill in foreign currency (CAD))
  DCT1 - VRN to DEN
  EHT3 prepaid DEN - YYC (Rate and bill in local currency (USD))
  DCT2 - DEN - MSY
  EHT4 collect MSY - YYC (Rate and bill in foreign currency (CAD))
  ICT - MSY - YYC

  3.Process EHT shipment to INV
  4. Create invoice that has a mix of freight revenue GL's, billing codes mapped to freight revenue and other GL's not mapped to freight revenue
  5.Finish the shipments by printing on AWBPRT

  7.In Origin consol screen, attach the HBLs to GC destined to gateway1

  15. Process a prepaid house truck shipment from gateway1 to final destination. Rate and bill in local currency (USD)
  16.In gateway1 consol, attach the original HBL and a new prepaid house truck shipment to a DC destined to gateway2

  25.Process MNFST, ICCOST, HBCOST and post MCTRAN
  26.Confim CFDATA is clear in gateway2
  27.Receive ShipLog at CFIT destination and post the consol settlement

name: Transcon_IC_DC_IC_MCCOST
description:
Create a happy path end-to-end automation script that runs in the given QA Environments without errors.
  Origin - QA3/VRN
  Gateway1- QA1/DEN
  Gateway2 - QA9/MSY
  Destination - QA4/YYC

  Steps:
  1.	Process a prepaid house truck shipment from origin VRN to final destination YYC. Rate and bill in local currency (EUR)
  2.	Process a collect house truck shipment from origin VRN to final destination YYC. Rate and bill in foreign currency (CAD)
  3.	Process EHT shipment to INV
  4.	Create invoice that has a mix of freight revenue GL's, billing codes mapped to freight revenue and other GL's not mapped to freight revenue
  5.	Finish the shipments by printing on AWBPRT
  6.	Confirm CFDATA is clear at Origin VRN
  7.	Attach the housebills to an IC destined to gateway1 DEN
  8.	Print the MNFST
  9.	Post MCTRAN
  10.	Find on IC reference in CFDATA and make sure it is clear
  11.	Receive ShipLog at gateway1 (DEN) CFIT and post the consol settlement
  12.	Receive ShipLog at final destination (YYC) CFIT and post the consol settlement
